body:
Please add a parameter to allow Cython to compile OpenMP on Windows using Visual Studio 2015 for Python 3.5 support that will automatically list those iterators for OpenMP 2.0, i.e. `ssize_t __pyx_t_2` and `ssize_t __pyx_t_3` instead of `size_t` for compatibility: 

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/37198246/cython-parallel-implementation-openmp-of-black-scholes-with-numpy-integrated-can

Since Microsoft has no intention of of upgrading OpenMP this seems like it would be a fairly simple workaround.

commit.message: add integrate demo and move comments
use string concatenation instead of string joining for 2-item f-strings
we actually know that FormattedValueNode always returns a Unicode string and no other object type => set node type accordingly
chaos benchmark working for cython v0.24
note embed and freeze now work for v0.24 3.5

Merge pull request #502 from phaustin/python3

Python3
avoid intermediate PyInt/Long creation when formatting C integer values
replace dead left-over code by the actually intended fast bint->True/False formatting implementation
assure constant declarations in bint->PyUnicode conversion code
generalise C type specific string formatting
implement somewhat useless but obvious and straight forward string conversion of the C error return type
implement width based format specs for integer formatting
avoid useless str() calls for unicode string formatting
avoid useless formatting operations when we know at compile time that the result is a Unicode string
add a simple benchmark for f-strings
avoid Cython's for-loop speed advantage in fstrings benchmark
Move complex type support into a utility code file.

Fix complex division for native complex type.

Implemented Smith's method, which avoid overflow for all but
the most extreme exponents. This agrees with what is used in NumPy.
support really long paddings in f-string formatting of C integers
Deprecate language as a special cythonize argument.
avoid code duplication in utility function by using macros

Fix timestamps option to work when generating a C++ output file and when
writing output file to a specified location.

Merge pull request #513 from insertinterestingnamehere/cpp_timestamps

Fix timestamps option to work when generating a C++ output file.

"ustring!s" (i.e. str(ustring)) is actually not safe to optimise away for f-string formatting in Py2 as it can fail to encode the Unicode string to a byte string. And it's unlikely to appear in practice.

title: Cython for Windows Visual Studio 2015 (Python 3.5) should have an option for OpenMP 2.0
